cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel parameter sharing mechanism for deep multi-task learning. The approach is evaluated on sequence labeling tasks, which are commonly studied in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the relationship between their approach and existing multi-task learning methods, which are also studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (AI) and neural networks (NE). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.NE are also likely sub-categories.
